#   18. REAL-ARTIFACT HARNESS II: provisioned workspaces (public input       #
#       files + instruction, train vs HIDDEN file checks), ToolActionLayer   #
#       with path guard and isolated-subprocess execution (-I, timeout,     #
#       trace + revert), csv / minimal-xlsx / json-logs / repo families,    #
#       reference runner.                                                    #
#   19. HETEROGENEOUS OBJECT DOMAINS (GDX): feature-level synthesis over    #
#       lists, strings, grids, dicts and graphs; universal / open-object /  #
#       emergent domains; residue-driven feature invention.                  #
#   20. SCOPED SELF-EDIT: the system patches the capability roster line in  #
#       a COPY of source, a guard proves only that line changed, and the    #
#       copy is evaluated in isolation.                                      #
#   21. PERSISTENT LONG-HORIZON CYCLE: checkpointed improvement cycles      #
#       with save/load state ("longcycle"; the original used a hype label    #
#       which is renamed here per the no-hype-labels rule).                  #
#                                                                             #
#   Adaptation renames (collision isolation, semantics unchanged):           #
#     SealedFileTask->ArtifactFileTask, ActionTrace->ArtifactActionTrace,    #
#     gd_features->gd_object_features, GD_FEATURES/_CONSTS/_BINARY_OPS->     #
#     GDX_*, _gd_numbers/_gd_pairs->_gdx_*, singularity->longcycle.          #
